WEBVTT

00:00.935 --> 00:04.203
♪♪

00:29.163 --> 00:31.864
Tell me
it's not true, liv.

00:44.812 --> 00:47.079
[ indistinct conversations ]

00:50.418 --> 00:52.151
Check, check.

00:52.153 --> 00:54.887
Woman: After years of false
starts and failed diplomacy,

00:54.889 --> 00:56.655
The impossible
now seems probably.

00:56.657 --> 00:58.357
A disarmament deal

00:58.359 --> 01:00.225
Between the united states
and the republic of bandar...

01:00.227 --> 01:01.827
It's never
gonna happen.
It will.

01:01.829 --> 01:02.761
Won't.
Will.

01:02.763 --> 01:03.829
Won't.
Will.

01:03.831 --> 01:05.564
Trust but verify.
We verified.

01:05.566 --> 01:08.400
An historic accord which
would end decades of sanctions

01:08.402 --> 01:09.835
Against the middle east nation

01:09.837 --> 01:11.904
In exchange for regulations
on its nuclear program.

01:11.906 --> 01:13.238
But i don't trust them.

01:13.240 --> 01:15.574
I don't either,
which is why we verified.

01:15.576 --> 01:17.609
I'm surprised
that you trust them, red.

01:17.611 --> 01:19.711
Negotiators who have been
working here all week

01:19.713 --> 01:21.847
Are said to have just a few
final details to iron out.

01:21.849 --> 01:23.949
If true,
presidents grant and razani

01:23.951 --> 01:26.285
Would sign their names
to the biggest push for peace

01:26.287 --> 01:28.454
Since the toppling
of the berlin wall.

01:28.456 --> 01:30.556
The bandaris have assured me
a thousand times

01:30.558 --> 01:32.257
Olivia pope
is not a problem.

01:32.259 --> 01:34.026
She slithered into the bed
of a married man.

01:34.028 --> 01:35.561
She's unclean.
She's a whore.

01:35.563 --> 01:36.595
You don't receive a whore.

01:36.597 --> 01:38.363
You married one.

01:38.365 --> 01:40.432
Very different situation.

01:40.434 --> 01:42.634
They won't receive her.
It's never going to happen.

01:47.741 --> 01:50.275
It just did.

01:50.277 --> 01:53.745
[ camera shutter clicking ]

01:53.747 --> 01:56.648
[ speaks farsi ]

01:56.650 --> 01:58.750
Male interpreter:
I'm always happy for
a chance to see ms. Pope.

01:58.752 --> 02:00.319
You say olivia's helped you
a lot over the years?

02:00.321 --> 02:03.822
[ translates in farsi ]

02:03.824 --> 02:06.291
The minister
is exaggerating.

02:06.293 --> 02:09.161
Once or twice,
maybe three times at the most.

02:09.163 --> 02:13.398
Female interpreter:
[ translates in farsi ]

02:13.400 --> 02:15.801
[ speaks farsi ]

02:19.740 --> 02:21.273
[ laughs ]

02:21.275 --> 02:23.308
She's helped both my family
and my country,

02:23.310 --> 02:25.944
But given how argumentative
my family is,

02:25.946 --> 02:27.846
I think she'd rather
just help my country.

02:27.848 --> 02:30.015
[ laughs ]
that is not true.

02:30.017 --> 02:30.949
Female interpreter:
[ translates in farsi ]

02:30.951 --> 02:33.085
Okay,
maybe a little true.

02:33.087 --> 02:34.653
[ laughter ]

02:34.655 --> 02:37.856
That sounds exactly like
how we do things over here.

02:37.858 --> 02:39.358
The president
gets all the credit

02:39.360 --> 02:40.626
While we do
all the work.

02:40.628 --> 02:43.562
[ translates in farsi ]

02:48.435 --> 02:51.837
[ both laugh ]

02:51.839 --> 02:53.672
Kill me now.

02:53.674 --> 02:55.774
Do not translate that.

02:55.776 --> 02:58.677
[ speaks farsi ]

02:58.679 --> 02:59.811
There's nothing better
than watching the game live.

02:59.813 --> 03:02.181
I agree.
Were you at wimbledon this year?

03:02.183 --> 03:03.715
Female interpreter:
[ translates in farsi ]

03:03.717 --> 03:06.718
Oh! [ gasps ]

03:06.720 --> 03:08.720
The ladies room is down the hall
and to the left.

03:08.722 --> 03:10.088
Don't worry.
I can translate for two.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.463
Unfortunately, i wasn't able to
make it to wimbledon this year,

03:18.465 --> 03:20.065
But i need your help.

03:24.238 --> 03:25.370
Excuse me?

03:33.814 --> 03:35.514
My niece
was getting married,

03:35.516 --> 03:36.648
Um, but my wife said

03:36.650 --> 03:38.650
That i couldn't ask her
to reschedule.

03:38.652 --> 03:40.652
I would like to defect.
Can you help me?

03:40.654 --> 03:43.255
[ chuckles ]

03:43.257 --> 03:45.891
I'm sure your niece was
very happy you were there.

03:45.893 --> 03:48.760
[ translates in farsi ]

03:48.762 --> 03:51.663
Would you like to meet the chef
before dessert comes out?

03:51.665 --> 03:54.266
[ translates in farsi ]

03:54.268 --> 03:56.768
He grew up
in the same province you did.

03:56.770 --> 03:58.270
[ translates in farsi ]

03:58.272 --> 03:59.271
Mm-hmm.

03:59.273 --> 04:02.441
I know he was very proud
to serve you.

04:02.443 --> 04:05.844
[ speaking farsi ]

04:05.846 --> 04:08.547
They're talking about his
family's olive farm in gorlan.

04:08.549 --> 04:10.716
I know.
You have 30 seconds. Go.

04:10.718 --> 04:12.684
I wish to defect
to the united states.
On what grounds?

04:12.686 --> 04:14.686
Human rights violations
my country is responsible for.

04:14.688 --> 04:16.121
Have you been
personally persecuted?

04:16.123 --> 04:17.289
No, but --
then i'm sorry,

04:17.291 --> 04:18.757
But there's nothing
the united states can do.

04:18.759 --> 04:21.793
Hey.
I've got information.

04:21.795 --> 04:24.229
About a nuclear facility your
country knows nothing about.

04:24.231 --> 04:26.365
I can give you the location,
but only if you offer me asylum.

04:28.202 --> 04:30.402
Okay, what kind of information
does he say he has?

04:30.404 --> 04:32.571
A location of a facility
we don't know about.

04:32.573 --> 04:34.439
It felt like
he was telling the truth.

04:34.441 --> 04:36.775
We used to get this all the time
from the soviets.

04:36.777 --> 04:38.110
Some guy touches down

04:38.112 --> 04:40.646
In the land of blue jeans
and miniskirts

04:40.648 --> 04:42.080
And immediately starts trying to
feed us a bunch of nonsense

04:42.082 --> 04:43.215
So he doesn't
have to go home.

04:43.217 --> 04:45.751
He didn't look smitten.
He looked scared.

04:45.753 --> 04:47.719
We're hours away
from an accord.

04:47.721 --> 04:51.056
Mr. President, an historic,
scandal-cleansing,

04:51.058 --> 04:54.826
Doves flying, angels singing,
reset button of an accord.

04:54.828 --> 04:58.563
We're on the verge
of restoring bandar as an ally

04:58.565 --> 05:00.065
In a region
where we have none.

05:00.067 --> 05:02.234
The deal's done.
Let's not blow this up.

05:02.236 --> 05:03.902
No one's saying
that we blow it up,

05:03.904 --> 05:05.504
Just that we find out
who navid is

05:05.506 --> 05:07.339
And what he might know.
What do we know
about him now?

05:07.341 --> 05:08.507
That he looks scared.

05:08.509 --> 05:10.075
I don't want the white house
anywhere near this.

05:10.077 --> 05:11.243
Exactly, sir.
It's crazy.

05:11.245 --> 05:12.344
That's why
my people should do it.

05:12.346 --> 05:13.578
Check him out,
find out if he has

05:13.580 --> 05:15.814
Any intelligence ties
or ulterior motives.

05:15.816 --> 05:17.816
We handle it quickly
and discreetly.

05:17.818 --> 05:19.518
We sign the accord
tomorrow afternoon.

05:19.520 --> 05:21.586
If there's anything to find,
find it before then.

05:25.592 --> 05:26.992
[ sighs ]

05:26.994 --> 05:31.163
Sir,
there is something...Else

05:31.165 --> 05:32.631
That we should probably
discuss.
[ door closes ]

05:32.633 --> 05:33.799
What's that?

05:33.801 --> 05:36.535
Rowan.
What about him?

05:36.537 --> 05:38.770
I'd like to get into this,
see how he managed to escape.

05:38.772 --> 05:41.273
Maybe run it through the c.I.A.,
homeland security.

05:41.275 --> 05:43.008
I told you
that wouldn't be necessary.

05:43.010 --> 05:44.042
It's being handled.

05:44.044 --> 05:47.512
Handled by whom,
may i ask?

05:49.016 --> 05:51.116
Anything else, cy?

05:59.226 --> 06:00.225
Are you okay?

06:00.227 --> 06:01.626
Why wouldn't i be okay?

06:01.628 --> 06:03.395
Because of what just happened
in the oval.

06:03.397 --> 06:04.663
I'm okay, red.

06:04.665 --> 06:07.466
We're living in a new world,
red.

06:07.468 --> 06:11.303
A world where olivia pope
is judge, jury, and executioner.

06:11.305 --> 06:14.840
She has his world, our world
hoisted on her shoulders.

06:14.842 --> 06:16.975
That is a fact.
There's no changing it.

06:16.977 --> 06:20.746
So, if the president is happy,
i'm happy.

06:20.748 --> 06:22.381
I serve at his pleasure.
I'm okay.

06:22.383 --> 06:24.716
What's your game plan?
David rosen.

06:24.718 --> 06:26.985
If you go to the
attorney general
for help yet again,

06:26.987 --> 06:28.520
The president
is gonna find out

06:28.522 --> 06:31.022
That you're doing exactly what
he just told you not to do.

06:31.024 --> 06:34.326
Which is why i'm not going
to the attorney general, red.

06:34.328 --> 06:36.294
The attorney general
is coming to me.

06:38.599 --> 06:40.098
You see?

06:40.100 --> 06:42.067
I'm okay.

06:42.069 --> 06:44.102
[ camera shutter clicking ]

06:44.104 --> 06:45.437
It's not a good time.

06:45.439 --> 06:46.738
Mellie:
We need to talk.

06:46.740 --> 06:48.206
About?
Our deal.

06:48.208 --> 06:49.708
We didn't have a deal.

06:49.710 --> 06:51.943
Do you really think i let
my son's murderer out of jail

06:51.945 --> 06:53.111
For nothing?

06:53.113 --> 06:55.380
I am not insane.
We had a deal.

06:55.382 --> 06:57.082
I help you, you help me.
We work together.

06:57.084 --> 06:58.583
I never agreed to that.

06:58.585 --> 06:59.851
I don't care
what you think you agreed to.

06:59.853 --> 07:01.086
That was the deal.

07:01.088 --> 07:02.921
And if you go back
on the deal,

07:02.923 --> 07:05.557
I'm gonna tell fitz
what we did.

07:05.559 --> 07:06.892
What<i> you</i> did.

07:06.894 --> 07:09.261
[ cellphone beeps ]

07:19.640 --> 07:21.706
Helen of troy.

07:27.648 --> 07:29.347
Hello.

07:36.457 --> 07:38.657
My people
are right upstairs.

07:38.659 --> 07:40.358
How is he?

07:53.640 --> 07:55.640
Olivia.

07:55.642 --> 07:57.008
Please.

08:00.948 --> 08:03.982
♪ i've been so many places ♪

08:03.984 --> 08:08.153
♪ in my life and time ♪

08:08.155 --> 08:10.355
You're wondering
why i'm here.

08:10.357 --> 08:11.690
Why are you here?

08:11.692 --> 08:13.091
Believe it or not,
i came to see your face.

08:13.093 --> 08:15.694
I don't believe you.

08:18.131 --> 08:21.500
I'm being hunted,
olivia.

08:21.502 --> 08:23.201
I know.

08:23.203 --> 08:25.170
By jake.

08:25.172 --> 08:29.074
Ballard?
He's...The least of my concerns.

08:30.777 --> 08:32.210
I warned you.

08:32.212 --> 08:36.147
You are convinced
that i am the devil,

08:36.149 --> 08:39.317
The man with his finger
on the button.

08:39.319 --> 08:41.686
Maybe i was,
but not anymore.

08:41.688 --> 08:43.355
You thought
that getting rid of me

08:43.357 --> 08:44.990
Would cause lilies
to sprout

08:44.992 --> 08:47.692
While mankind locked arms
in a collective embrace

08:47.694 --> 08:50.195
And sang joyously
to never-ending world peace.

08:50.197 --> 08:51.463
You were wrong.

08:51.465 --> 08:53.064
I am out,

08:53.066 --> 08:59.471
And now there's just...
Some other devil in my stead,

08:59.473 --> 09:02.541
Someone else with their finger
on the button.

09:02.543 --> 09:04.743
Someone far more dangerous
than i.

09:04.745 --> 09:09.881
My sons...

09:09.883 --> 09:12.484
Have turned against me.

09:12.486 --> 09:14.920
That's not my concern.

09:14.922 --> 09:16.755
Not yet,
but you should be afraid.
Why?

09:16.757 --> 09:20.559
Because i am afraid.

09:20.561 --> 09:24.963
♪ of a true love
while holding nothing ♪

09:27.668 --> 09:29.534
What are you
talking about?

09:29.536 --> 09:30.835
[ sighs ]

09:30.837 --> 09:32.571
As long as i am alive,

09:32.573 --> 09:36.741
I will do my best to make sure
that you are protected,

09:36.743 --> 09:41.079
But in the event
of my death...

09:41.081 --> 09:45.417
I have already given you
everything you need to survive.

09:45.419 --> 09:48.954
♪ listen to the melody ♪

09:48.956 --> 09:50.188
♪ 'cause my love... ♪

09:50.190 --> 09:52.357
Dad --
you should know,

09:52.359 --> 09:55.594
I hope you know...

09:55.596 --> 09:57.662
I did my best for you.

10:01.268 --> 10:03.168
Olivia.

10:08.609 --> 10:15.547
I take tremendous pride
in who you have become.

10:23.490 --> 10:27.459
♪ i love you in a place ♪

10:27.461 --> 10:29.894
♪ where there's
no space or time ♪

10:36.770 --> 10:38.803
Have you heard of
something called lazarus one?

10:38.805 --> 10:41.106
Lazarus one?

10:41.108 --> 10:43.508
My father said
some of his people,

10:43.510 --> 10:47.912
His sons have turned against him
and initiated a plan.

10:47.914 --> 10:50.015
They're trying
to kill him.

10:50.017 --> 10:52.617
Never heard of it.

10:52.619 --> 10:55.186
But i wish them luck.

10:55.188 --> 10:57.922
Marcus: Let's do this.
Navid turani.

10:57.924 --> 11:00.291
Official translator
for the government of bandar.

11:00.293 --> 11:02.327
Grew up in a rural village
in the bandari mountains.

11:02.329 --> 11:03.528
Pace.

11:03.530 --> 11:05.530
And won a scholarship
to a school in the cap--

11:05.532 --> 11:07.032
Faster.
Quinn.

11:07.034 --> 11:08.800
Wha-- he's going slow.
You're going too slow.

11:08.802 --> 11:11.202
Olivia: He's fine. Don't worry.
You'll get your sandbox back.

11:11.204 --> 11:12.437
As i was saying,

11:12.439 --> 11:14.339
Navid was awarded
a full academic scholarship.

11:14.341 --> 11:17.042
There was a time in bandar
before razani took power

11:17.044 --> 11:19.377
Where a kid from a poor village
could learn english,

11:19.379 --> 11:21.179
Read the classics,
and make something of himself.

11:21.181 --> 11:22.881
Bandar still has the highest
literacy rate in the region.

11:22.883 --> 11:24.215
No thanks to razani.

11:24.217 --> 11:26.017
Navid translated
for bandari dignitaries

11:26.019 --> 11:27.686
At the middle east
peace summit,

11:27.688 --> 11:30.021
State visits to london,
paris, moscow.

11:30.023 --> 11:31.056
Does he always work
for the same person?

11:31.058 --> 11:33.024
Not always,
but he's usually paired

11:33.026 --> 11:35.794
With minister of energy
farshad khansari.

11:35.796 --> 11:36.961
That's who he was translating
for when he reached out to me.

11:36.963 --> 11:38.363
Then he's probably
been privy

11:38.365 --> 11:39.998
To some highly classified
conversations.

11:40.000 --> 11:41.566
He's been at every
u.N. Weapons inspection

11:41.568 --> 11:43.068
Since the program started
in 2003.

11:43.070 --> 11:46.805
And now he wants out.
Any chance this guy's a spy?

11:46.807 --> 11:48.206
No hits on qr-18.

11:48.208 --> 11:50.008
No mentions of him
in any of the chatter.

11:50.010 --> 11:51.843
Looks like he's just a guy
who wants to get out.

11:51.845 --> 11:53.378
So, let's see
what this guy has to say.

11:53.380 --> 11:54.412
If we want to talk to him,
we have to get him alone first.

11:54.414 --> 11:55.980
Which won't be easy.

11:55.982 --> 11:58.349
If he's not working,
he's under lock and key
at their embassy.

11:58.351 --> 11:59.417
Huck.

11:59.419 --> 12:00.385
I got this.

12:01.521 --> 12:02.987
[ camera shutter clicking ]

12:02.989 --> 12:04.989
Fitz: President razani,
the united states has no issue

12:04.991 --> 12:06.825
With a peaceful
scientific nuclear program.

12:06.827 --> 12:09.728
However, we must ensure
that under no circumstances

12:09.730 --> 12:12.931
Will bandar ever seek, develop,
or acquire nuclear weapons.

12:12.933 --> 12:14.799
Interpreter: [ speaking farsi ]

12:17.370 --> 12:19.704
[ siren wailing ]

12:19.706 --> 12:21.539
Should've warned me

12:21.541 --> 12:23.408
Not to take the pill you gave me
on an empty stomach.

12:23.410 --> 12:26.611
You'll be fine.
I've spoken with the president.

12:26.613 --> 12:29.714
He's agreed to offer you asylum,
assuming your intel checks out.

12:29.716 --> 12:31.116
Get me somewhere safe,

12:31.118 --> 12:32.917
I'll tell you all i know,
promise.

12:32.919 --> 12:34.352
I'm sorry, but it's not
gonna work that way.

12:34.354 --> 12:37.422
You talk
then you get asylum.

12:39.893 --> 12:42.761
I can't.

12:42.763 --> 12:45.597
This regime, razani,

12:45.599 --> 12:48.133
It's not like it once was
in bandar.

12:48.135 --> 12:51.035
He will kill anyone
he even suspects opposes him.

12:51.037 --> 12:53.571
I've already said too much.

12:53.573 --> 12:55.807
I promise that if you're
telling the truth,

12:55.809 --> 12:58.109
You will never have to
go back there ever again.

12:58.111 --> 13:01.379
[ sighs ]

13:03.550 --> 13:06.484
The framework calls for bandar
to allow inspections

13:06.486 --> 13:08.419
At all nuclear facilities,
but --

13:08.421 --> 13:10.622
But there's
a secret facility.

13:10.624 --> 13:13.491
And razani toured the facility
three months ago.

13:13.493 --> 13:14.793
Where is it?

13:17.297 --> 13:20.298
It's five miles south
of yabreen.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.333
It's in the desert.

13:22.335 --> 13:25.136
All right, if this checks out,
you'll have your asylum.

13:26.640 --> 13:29.307
I'm a little lost.

13:29.309 --> 13:32.410
We need 12 hours to verify
the translator's intel.

13:32.412 --> 13:33.344
I got that.

13:33.346 --> 13:34.679
And it can't look like
i'm stalling

13:34.681 --> 13:36.181
Or stepping away
from the negotiating table.

13:36.183 --> 13:38.016
I got that, too.

13:38.018 --> 13:40.652
So...What you need from me
is...?

13:40.654 --> 13:42.253
Time.

13:42.255 --> 13:43.788
I need you to stall.

13:43.790 --> 13:48.326
See, that right there,
that's where i get lost.

13:48.328 --> 13:52.430
I've got zero, zippo, nada
to do with these negotiations

13:52.432 --> 13:53.832
Other than cheering them on
from the sideline --

13:53.834 --> 13:55.800
If you were
to let it slip

13:55.802 --> 13:57.302
That you had reservations
about the treaty --

13:57.304 --> 13:59.470
But i don't.
I assure you, mr. President --

13:59.472 --> 14:00.705
But if you did.

14:00.707 --> 14:02.106
[ scoffs ]

14:02.108 --> 14:04.142
I certainly wouldn't
voice them publicly.

14:04.144 --> 14:07.512
But if you did
voice them publicly,

14:07.514 --> 14:09.380
That might
slow things down,

14:09.382 --> 14:11.449
Give us time
to verify the intel.

14:13.453 --> 14:15.787
You want me
to put my foot in my mouth?

14:15.789 --> 14:18.089
Yes, susan.
I do.

14:19.626 --> 14:21.893
Oh, why didn't you say so?

14:21.895 --> 14:24.696
♪♪

14:29.736 --> 14:32.036
[ crowd shouting ]

14:32.038 --> 14:34.672
Eyes forward,
ignore questions.

14:34.674 --> 14:36.140
Straight
to the building.
Uh-huh.

14:36.142 --> 14:38.042
Woman:
Madam vice president,

14:38.044 --> 14:39.811
Are you pleased with the terms
of the nuclear treaty?

14:39.813 --> 14:41.079
I've read it thoroughly.

14:41.081 --> 14:43.314
I think it's a good
and fair treaty.

14:43.316 --> 14:45.216
But i'd like it
a whole lot better

14:45.218 --> 14:47.218
If those 12 million girls
in bandar

14:47.220 --> 14:48.553
Were allowed
to go to school,

14:48.555 --> 14:50.521
Allowed to learn
to read and write

14:50.523 --> 14:52.657
And voice their own opinions
on this treaty.

14:52.659 --> 14:54.092
I think
that would make it better.

14:54.094 --> 14:55.927
But what do i know?

14:55.929 --> 14:57.695
I'm just a woman.

14:57.697 --> 14:59.764
A woman a heartbeat away
from the presidency.

14:59.766 --> 15:02.200
Man: Sources confirm
that susan ross' remarks

15:02.202 --> 15:05.103
Have caused president razani
to step away from negotiations,

15:05.105 --> 15:07.505
Putting the u.S.-Bandari
nuclear treaty on ice.

15:07.507 --> 15:09.774
I need you to create
a task force.

15:09.776 --> 15:10.942
Task force?

15:10.944 --> 15:13.511
Yes, a task force,
a committee,

15:13.513 --> 15:15.780
A panel
on parole loopholes.

15:15.782 --> 15:18.950
Federal
sentencing issues.

15:18.952 --> 15:20.451
Those aren't
the same thing.

15:20.453 --> 15:23.288
Whatever flaw
in our criminal justice system

15:23.290 --> 15:26.090
That allowed for eli pope
to walk out of a federal prison.

15:26.092 --> 15:28.693
I'm sorry, eli pope?
Rowan is out of prison?

15:28.695 --> 15:30.595
You didn't know.

15:30.597 --> 15:32.030
Does it look like i knew?

15:32.032 --> 15:34.432
How?
No clue.

15:34.434 --> 15:37.035
Task force, committee, panel,
the reason you're standing here.

15:37.037 --> 15:38.736
We shouldn't be setting up
a task force

15:38.738 --> 15:40.939
To close loopholes
so other sociopathic terrorists

15:40.941 --> 15:42.707
Don't get released
on technicalities.

15:42.709 --> 15:44.242
I mean, we should,

15:44.244 --> 15:46.077
But first we should do
everything in our power

15:46.079 --> 15:48.947
To find rowan
and return him to a cement box.

15:48.949 --> 15:50.381
The fbi
should be on this.

15:50.383 --> 15:51.916
If you think so.

15:51.918 --> 15:54.752
In fact, we need to bring in all
of the intelligence agencies,

15:54.754 --> 15:56.654
Marshal every resource
at our disposal.

15:56.656 --> 15:59.457
If that's the path
the justice department
wants to take.

15:59.459 --> 16:00.825
I'll get on it right now.

16:00.827 --> 16:02.260
Whatever you think is best,
rosen.

16:02.262 --> 16:05.730
[ door opens, closes ]

16:05.732 --> 16:07.999
You can go right in,
captain ballard.

16:15.675 --> 16:17.675
The president
wanted to see me.

16:17.677 --> 16:20.011
The president is busy
with the bandari negotiations.

16:20.013 --> 16:21.579
Ah.

16:21.581 --> 16:23.982
So, you just thought you'd
exercise executive privilege

16:23.984 --> 16:25.783
And have me summoned
to the oval office?

16:25.785 --> 16:27.418
I needed
to ask you something.

16:27.420 --> 16:30.121
You understand how much i do not
care about what you need?

16:30.123 --> 16:32.190
I do,
but this isn't for me.

16:33.093 --> 16:34.826
He contacted you?

16:34.828 --> 16:35.994
Came to my office.

16:35.996 --> 16:37.028
What did he say?

16:37.030 --> 16:39.130
Someone's trying
to kill him,

16:39.132 --> 16:41.332
And i think he's actually
the innocent one this time.

16:43.470 --> 16:44.836
Right.

16:44.838 --> 16:47.138
Jake, i looked
into my father's eyes,

16:47.140 --> 16:49.440
And i saw something
i have never seen before.

16:49.442 --> 16:51.676
What's that?

16:51.678 --> 16:52.510
Fear.

16:52.512 --> 16:53.811
[ laughs ]

16:53.813 --> 16:55.613
Jake.

16:55.615 --> 17:00.184
Have you ever...
Lied to someone's face

17:00.186 --> 17:02.687
When your back was
completely against the wall

17:02.689 --> 17:04.055
To get what you wanted?

17:04.057 --> 17:09.227
Have you ever
looked someone in the eye

17:09.229 --> 17:10.962
And made them think
you loved them?

17:10.964 --> 17:14.832
Really truly loved them

17:14.834 --> 17:18.903
So you could take whatever it is
you needed from them?

17:20.407 --> 17:22.373
I believe him.

17:22.375 --> 17:26.744
My gut says
he's telling the truth.

17:26.746 --> 17:28.379
Of course it does.

17:28.381 --> 17:31.015
Otherwise you'd be a fool
with daddy issues

17:31.017 --> 17:33.184
Who just got played
by a mass murderer.

17:33.186 --> 17:35.053
What if he is innocent

17:35.055 --> 17:36.921
And someone really is trying
to kill him?

17:36.923 --> 17:38.256
Honestly, liv,

17:38.258 --> 17:40.825
I just hope i get to him
before they do.

17:47.500 --> 17:50.068
What did you think?

17:50.070 --> 17:54.705
That i'd come here
and spoon you?

17:54.707 --> 17:56.174
Give you a shoulder
to cry on,

17:56.176 --> 17:57.375
Listen to you talk about

17:57.377 --> 18:01.212
All the dark places
rowan built inside of you?

18:01.214 --> 18:03.581
That train
has left the station,

18:03.583 --> 18:05.917
And you do not
get to ride this anymore.

18:05.919 --> 18:07.185
If you want someone
to talk to,

18:07.187 --> 18:08.453
Tell your boyfriend

18:08.455 --> 18:10.855
That you just let
his son's killer out of prison.

18:10.857 --> 18:11.989
See how that works out.

18:14.227 --> 18:16.461
Jake,
i am going to tell him.

18:16.463 --> 18:17.695
You are?

18:17.697 --> 18:20.932
That i'd like to see.

18:20.934 --> 18:23.568
I was supposed to
choose you.

18:23.570 --> 18:25.136
What?

18:25.138 --> 18:27.071
When you told me
fitz loved me

18:27.073 --> 18:28.940
And that
i should go to him,

18:28.942 --> 18:30.641
What you really meant was

18:30.643 --> 18:35.246
That you wanted me
to say i didn't love him and...

18:35.248 --> 18:37.281
I was supposed to
choose you.

18:37.283 --> 18:39.984
No, you were supposed to be
too good for me.

18:39.986 --> 18:42.887
It never crossed my mind that
i would be too good for you.

18:42.889 --> 18:44.455
The things, the crimes,

18:44.457 --> 18:46.624
The violence
i have forgiven you for,

18:46.626 --> 18:48.392
And you won't even consider
that maybe i --

18:48.394 --> 18:50.561
Jake.

18:50.563 --> 18:52.130
This is a surprise.

18:52.132 --> 18:53.731
Mr. President.

18:53.733 --> 18:58.269
Jake was just here to...
Fill us in on my father.

18:58.271 --> 19:00.471
Any news?
Did you find him?

19:00.473 --> 19:01.739
No, sir.
Not yet.

19:01.741 --> 19:03.541
But don't worry.
I'm gonna keep looking.

19:12.352 --> 19:13.618
Stop.

19:13.620 --> 19:14.785
I'm not saying anything.

19:14.787 --> 19:16.854
You're looking at me.

19:16.856 --> 19:19.123
I'm going to tell him.
Of course you are.
You have to tell him.

19:19.125 --> 19:20.424
I just said that.
Before it's too late.

19:20.426 --> 19:22.093
Which is
what i told you.

19:24.797 --> 19:26.597
If he finds out
from anyone else

19:26.599 --> 19:28.533
That it was you who got
your father out of prison --

19:28.535 --> 19:29.767
Abigail!

19:32.305 --> 19:36.374
Cyrus is working with david
behind the president's back.

19:36.376 --> 19:39.944
Yeah. He used
some jedi mind trick

19:39.946 --> 19:42.380
To convince david
to call in the fbi
to hunt your dad.

19:42.382 --> 19:43.614
I did some digging,

19:43.616 --> 19:47.552
And it's only a matter of time,
liv, so...

19:47.554 --> 19:48.319
I have to tell him.

19:48.321 --> 19:49.820
Yeah.

19:49.822 --> 19:50.888
I'm going to tell him.

19:50.890 --> 19:52.223
I'm going to tell him
everything.

19:52.225 --> 19:53.691
I can't lie to him.

19:53.693 --> 19:56.527
It's...Pressing on me.

19:56.529 --> 19:58.829
It's like a weight.

19:58.831 --> 20:00.998
But...

20:01.000 --> 20:05.136
Once i tell him,
that's it.

20:05.138 --> 20:07.338
He will not forgive this.

20:07.340 --> 20:10.241
When i tell him...
It's over.

20:10.243 --> 20:11.642
It's done.
We're done.

20:18.518 --> 20:21.319
I'm not ready to be done.

20:21.321 --> 20:23.487
[ cellphone ringing ]

20:23.489 --> 20:26.257
[ sighs ]

20:30.363 --> 20:31.362
[ cellphone beeps ]

20:31.364 --> 20:33.064
Quinn.
We have a problem.

20:33.066 --> 20:35.166
That location
navid gave you --

20:35.168 --> 20:37.001
Definitely not
a secret weapons facility, liv.

20:37.003 --> 20:38.569
His intel is bogus.

20:39.872 --> 20:41.339
[ door slams ]
you lied to us.

20:41.341 --> 20:42.607
What?

20:42.609 --> 20:44.508
That location
five miles south of yabreen,

20:44.510 --> 20:46.711
It isn't some secret
nuclear weapons site, navid.

20:46.713 --> 20:49.780
It's just some old soda factory.
You lied to us!

20:49.782 --> 20:51.682
This can't be right.
We checked.

20:51.684 --> 20:53.551
Well, check again.
I didn't lie.

20:53.553 --> 20:55.419
I remember them
talking about an attack

20:55.421 --> 20:57.088
From the place
in this photo.

20:57.090 --> 20:58.289
Your people will never know
you came to me.

20:58.291 --> 20:59.957
Ms. Pope.
'cause i will
keep this quiet.

20:59.959 --> 21:01.859
And tomorrow morning,
you will be released
from this hospital.

21:01.861 --> 21:04.562
I cannot go back
to my country.
Your asylum has been denied.

21:04.564 --> 21:06.864
I have stationed a guard
outside your room.

21:06.866 --> 21:09.700
He will make sure
that you do not try to leave.
What?

21:09.702 --> 21:10.735
I'm very sorry, navid.

21:10.737 --> 21:12.169
There's nothing
i can do for you.

21:17.310 --> 21:19.243
[ camera shutter clicking ]

21:19.245 --> 21:21.746
Huck, it's jake.
Safe house was a dead end.

21:21.748 --> 21:23.214
Rowan wasn't there.

21:23.216 --> 21:24.982
Call me back
if you have any other leads.

21:24.984 --> 21:28.552
Security cams have them leaving
the building at 8:47 p.M.

21:28.554 --> 21:30.388
Who's the car
registered to?

21:30.390 --> 21:32.957
Some nobody who flew to athens
last night for a wedding.

21:32.959 --> 21:35.626
My guess is they lifted it
from an airport parking garage

21:35.628 --> 21:37.061
So no one would know
it was missing.

21:37.063 --> 21:40.164
Someone activated
lazarus one.

21:40.166 --> 21:41.799
Is that what all of this
is really about?

21:41.801 --> 21:44.101
You get the traffic cams?

21:44.103 --> 21:47.305
Yeah. All major intersections
within a five-mile radius.

21:47.307 --> 21:50.274
I'll run it through qr-18,
see where rowan leads us.

21:50.276 --> 21:52.176
Not we. You.

21:52.178 --> 21:53.477
You said on the phone
you'd help me with this.

21:53.479 --> 21:55.079
I said
i'd get you intel.
Huck.

21:55.081 --> 21:56.180
Your guy is out.

21:56.182 --> 21:57.181
My guy?

21:57.183 --> 21:58.849
Your beast.
I can see it in your eyes.

21:58.851 --> 22:00.351
This isn't just a job
for you.

22:00.353 --> 22:01.619
Oh, please.

22:01.621 --> 22:03.154
I can't
be around that jake.

22:03.156 --> 22:05.823
I've spent too much time
putting my own guy
back in his cage.

22:05.825 --> 22:07.291
If i go down this road
with you --

22:07.293 --> 22:09.126
It's rowan, huck.

22:09.128 --> 22:11.429
You see a cockroach,
you step on it!

22:11.431 --> 22:12.863
Not me.

22:12.865 --> 22:14.965
Once i open that door,
there's no closing it again.

22:14.967 --> 22:17.535
I helped you with the intel,
but that's it.

22:17.537 --> 22:19.070
From here on out,
you're on your own.

22:21.341 --> 22:23.407
[ camera shutter clicking ]

22:33.052 --> 22:35.052
Can i ask
what you're thinking about?

22:37.890 --> 22:39.290
No.

23:02.749 --> 23:04.715
You want to watch tv?

23:10.089 --> 23:12.256
I'm fine here.

23:32.545 --> 23:34.011
Got a minute?
No.

23:34.013 --> 23:35.179
Got 10?

23:42.121 --> 23:43.387
[ scoffs ]

23:43.389 --> 23:45.589
What the hell am i doing?

23:45.591 --> 23:47.091
Huh?

23:47.093 --> 23:48.426
You ever have a moment

23:48.428 --> 23:50.294
When you realize your life
is nothing like it was

23:50.296 --> 23:52.062
And nothing like
you wanted it to be?

23:52.064 --> 23:54.398
That moment
is right now?
Yeah.

23:54.400 --> 23:55.633
After we just had sex?

23:55.635 --> 23:56.934
I was chief of staff

23:56.936 --> 23:59.103
To the most powerful man
in the world.

23:59.105 --> 24:00.971
I had a seat
next to the throne.

24:00.973 --> 24:04.742
Now i'm an overpaid babysitter
for the queen of the nerds.

24:04.744 --> 24:05.976
Give her some time.

24:05.978 --> 24:07.611
I was unpolished
when i became

24:07.613 --> 24:09.547
The attorney general
of the united states,

24:09.549 --> 24:11.849
But look at me now.

24:15.988 --> 24:18.289
[ camera shutter clicking ]

24:18.291 --> 24:19.557
[ door opens ]

24:19.559 --> 24:20.758
Where have you been?

24:20.760 --> 24:21.826
[ door closes ]
huck: Out.

24:21.828 --> 24:23.227
Out?
Out.

24:23.229 --> 24:25.629
Navid's story
didn't hold?

24:25.631 --> 24:28.332
Atmospheric data shows
nothing nuclear in that area.

24:28.334 --> 24:30.134
He was lying.

24:30.136 --> 24:31.168
Marcus:
I feel sorry for him.

24:31.170 --> 24:32.603
He lied.

24:32.605 --> 24:34.171
'cause he was desperate.
Doesn't make it right.

24:34.173 --> 24:36.006
He made a mistake.
You never made a mistake?

24:36.008 --> 24:37.942
I went to law school.
I regret that.

24:37.944 --> 24:39.477
Point is i wouldn't want to
go back to bandar, either,

24:39.479 --> 24:41.679
And i might make up some stuff
so i didn't have to.

24:41.681 --> 24:43.314
Now, would i choose
a soda factory

24:43.316 --> 24:45.115
As my secret weapons
nuclear facility?

24:45.117 --> 24:47.084
I'd like to think
i would not.

24:47.086 --> 24:48.819
They never move.
What?

24:48.821 --> 24:50.855
You see these delivery trucks
out front here?

24:50.857 --> 24:52.756
[ camera shutter clicking ]

24:52.758 --> 24:53.924
Yeah.

24:53.926 --> 24:55.659
They never move.

24:55.661 --> 24:58.429
Week after week after week,
they're in the exact same place.

24:58.431 --> 25:00.264
But over here
on this side of the building,

25:00.266 --> 25:02.166
Water tankers are moving
in and out all the time.

25:02.168 --> 25:04.468
Wait, so they're bringing water
into the building,

25:04.470 --> 25:05.703
But nothing is going out?

25:05.705 --> 25:07.371
What does that mean?

25:07.373 --> 25:08.239
It means that's not
a soda factory.

25:10.543 --> 25:12.142
He wasn't lying.

25:12.144 --> 25:13.777
What?
Navid.

25:13.779 --> 25:15.212
What are you
talking about?
It isn't a soda factory.

25:15.214 --> 25:16.547
They just want us
to think that.

25:16.549 --> 25:18.182
Huck hacked
the power grid,

25:18.184 --> 25:19.283
And the amount of electricity
they're using in that building,

25:19.285 --> 25:20.551
It's massive.

25:20.553 --> 25:22.186
You could literally
buy the whole world a coke

25:22.188 --> 25:23.654
If you were actually making soda
in there.

25:23.656 --> 25:25.322
What is it, then?
Huck:
They're cooling something.

25:25.324 --> 25:26.457
It might not be nuclear,
but it's something,

25:26.459 --> 25:27.691
And they're trying
to keep it a secret.

25:27.693 --> 25:29.860
We think
navid was right.

25:33.032 --> 25:34.899
[ sighs ]

25:34.901 --> 25:38.035
White house sources indicate
that bandari president razani

25:38.037 --> 25:40.371
Has accepted
the vice president's apology

25:40.373 --> 25:43.073
And has already returned
to the negotiation table.

25:43.075 --> 25:45.309
Barring another
unforeseen delay,

25:45.311 --> 25:47.711
President grant's landmark
nuclear arms agreement

25:47.713 --> 25:49.213
With bandar

25:49.215 --> 25:52.316
Is all set to be signed
as early as this afternoon.

25:52.318 --> 25:54.685
[ camera shutters clicking ]

25:54.687 --> 25:57.488
♪♪

26:00.326 --> 26:03.127
[ cellphone vibrating ]

26:14.407 --> 26:16.941
[ vibrating continues ]

26:21.013 --> 26:22.379
Olivia:
Stop the signing.

26:22.381 --> 26:24.582
Liv, what?

26:24.584 --> 26:27.184
They're hiding something.
Do not let fitz sign that deal.

26:27.186 --> 26:30.588
[ camera shutters clicking ]

26:30.590 --> 26:31.889
I can't.

26:31.891 --> 26:34.725
You can. You have to.
Trust me, abby.

26:34.727 --> 26:36.627
I need to get navid before
he leaves this hospital.
You can do this.

26:36.629 --> 26:38.996
Do it. Now!

26:48.641 --> 26:50.407
[ clears throat ]

26:50.409 --> 26:51.575
Abby?

26:51.577 --> 26:53.110
Mr. President,
we have a situation.

26:56.449 --> 26:59.817
Liv's gut was right.
Navid is telling the truth.

26:59.819 --> 27:02.720
[ camera shutters clicking ]

27:02.722 --> 27:05.556
♪♪

27:28.180 --> 27:29.880
[ soft groan ]

27:35.321 --> 27:36.320
[ gasps ]

27:36.322 --> 27:38.856
[ groaning ]

27:38.858 --> 27:40.457
Why did president grant
suddenly break off talks?

27:40.459 --> 27:43.260
Nothing is broken.
This deal is very much intact.

27:43.262 --> 27:46.463
Help. Help.

27:46.465 --> 27:49.333
Help! We need help!
Somebody!

27:49.335 --> 27:51.268
Why did the president
just walk away from --

27:51.270 --> 27:52.703
This agreement has been months
in the making.

27:52.705 --> 27:54.238
Isn't it worth taking the time
to get it right?

27:55.875 --> 27:57.708
Help.

28:02.348 --> 28:05.983
[ monitor beeping ]

28:05.985 --> 28:08.185
Hello.

28:08.187 --> 28:12.156
The doctors said
you're gonna be all right.

28:12.158 --> 28:15.325
I tried finding
a number to call,

28:15.327 --> 28:19.396
A family member,
an emergency contact, but --

28:19.398 --> 28:21.131
Told you,
i don't have anyone.

28:24.704 --> 28:27.337
I just got off the phone

28:27.339 --> 28:29.406
With a friend of mine
at the white house.

28:29.408 --> 28:32.142
She was able to track down
your old phone records.

28:32.144 --> 28:35.079
I saw all the calls you made
to an amir.

28:40.152 --> 28:42.386
Navid.

28:42.388 --> 28:44.388
It's okay.

28:44.390 --> 28:46.824
No one else knows.
No one else has to know.

28:48.828 --> 28:51.528
[ voice breaking ] do you know
what they do to gay people

28:51.530 --> 28:52.629
In my country, ms. Pope?

28:56.569 --> 29:00.204
Being born different
is a crime punishable by death.

29:00.206 --> 29:02.706
Coming here
was supposed to be my chance

29:02.708 --> 29:07.010
Of living a life
free of secrets.

29:07.012 --> 29:10.881
No more watching what i say,
watching what i do.

29:10.883 --> 29:12.750
No more scheming.

29:12.752 --> 29:15.185
No more hiding.

29:17.356 --> 29:20.290
I'm sorry
about all the blood,

29:20.292 --> 29:22.693
But if i was sent back
to my country,

29:22.695 --> 29:24.995
I'm dead anyway.

29:28.267 --> 29:30.701
The location you gave me
is not some old soda factory.

29:30.703 --> 29:32.269
It's something else.

29:32.271 --> 29:35.272
Something else the bandaris
don't want us knowing about.

29:35.274 --> 29:37.207
You were right.

29:37.209 --> 29:38.809
Are you saying --

29:38.811 --> 29:41.445
I should have listened to you.
I should have believed you.

29:41.447 --> 29:44.047
[ sobs ]

29:46.819 --> 29:48.886
[ camera shutter clicking ]

29:48.888 --> 29:51.955
[ indistinct conversations ]

29:58.831 --> 29:59.897
Susan.
David.

29:59.899 --> 30:01.331
How are you?
Good.

30:01.333 --> 30:02.633
What are you doing
in the white house?

30:02.635 --> 30:04.668
No, wait.
Let me guess.

30:04.670 --> 30:06.436
You're...

30:06.438 --> 30:09.239
Are you actually gues--
i don't really have
a guess.

30:09.241 --> 30:10.841
I'm meeting
with cyrus beene.

30:10.843 --> 30:12.576
I saw your statement.

30:12.578 --> 30:13.744
My apology.

30:13.746 --> 30:15.078
I wish
it wasn't an apology.

30:15.080 --> 30:16.680
Well, i shouldn't have said
what i said.

30:16.682 --> 30:17.848
Oh, i liked
what you said.

30:17.850 --> 30:19.249
You did?
It was honest.

30:19.251 --> 30:20.350
That's true.

30:20.352 --> 30:21.985
And it was true.
True.

30:21.987 --> 30:24.955
You should never apologize
for being you.

30:24.957 --> 30:26.957
Thank you.

30:26.959 --> 30:28.258
Which way are you headed?

30:28.260 --> 30:30.627
I'm headed that way,
and i should go.

30:30.629 --> 30:32.029
Nice to run into you.

30:37.136 --> 30:39.002
[ door closes ]

30:46.946 --> 30:48.378
What's this?

30:48.380 --> 30:50.614
The answer to the question.
It's all here.

30:50.616 --> 30:52.850
Question?
What question?
Eli pope's escape.

30:52.852 --> 30:54.184
Right, right.

30:54.186 --> 30:56.720
Forgot.
You were looking into that.

30:56.722 --> 30:58.689
I should say that none of this
is conclusive.

30:58.691 --> 31:00.991
None of the suspects
have been questioned about this.

31:00.993 --> 31:02.993
Is this interesting?
You're making this
sound interesting.

31:02.995 --> 31:04.661
It doesn't make
a whole lot of sense.

31:04.663 --> 31:06.196
Even more interesting.

31:06.198 --> 31:08.699
Well, the suspense
is almost intriguing me.

31:08.701 --> 31:10.033
Who's the mastermind?

31:10.035 --> 31:11.368
Olivia pope.

31:18.344 --> 31:19.776
Olivia?

31:21.580 --> 31:23.313
You sure?

31:23.315 --> 31:25.482
Agents are bringing her in
even as we speak.

31:25.484 --> 31:27.484
Man: Ms. Olivia pope?

31:27.486 --> 31:29.419
Fbi.

31:29.421 --> 31:31.722
I had no idea that going down
this road would lead to olivia.

31:31.724 --> 31:32.856
Who could have?

31:32.858 --> 31:34.391
I have a warrant signed

31:34.393 --> 31:36.059
By the attorney general
of the united states.

31:36.061 --> 31:37.394
Cyrus:
Does the president know?

31:37.396 --> 31:39.162
Do<i> you</i> want to
break it to him?

31:39.164 --> 31:42.699
You're arresting me?
On what grounds?

31:42.701 --> 31:44.368
Might be better
coming from a friend.

31:44.370 --> 31:46.203
Aiding the escape
of a prisoner.

31:46.205 --> 31:47.137
Please turn around.

31:49.775 --> 31:50.941
[ handcuffs click ]

31:53.245 --> 31:54.611
[ sighs ]

32:02.855 --> 32:05.756
♪♪

32:17.236 --> 32:18.936
Give me the keys.

32:18.938 --> 32:20.804
[ keys jingling ]

32:41.760 --> 32:45.662
They told me
you let rowan out.

32:45.664 --> 32:48.298
But that's insane, right?
That's impossible.

32:50.402 --> 32:54.905
You wouldn't do that.
I know you wouldn't do that.

32:54.907 --> 32:58.275
You wouldn't do that
to me.

32:58.277 --> 33:00.243
You're not mellie.

33:00.245 --> 33:03.447
I don't understand
how this happened,

33:03.449 --> 33:06.083
And i'm going to find out,
but i know it wasn't you.

33:06.085 --> 33:07.918
Right?

33:10.622 --> 33:13.023
Olivia.

33:15.861 --> 33:18.061
Tell me it's not true.

33:23.669 --> 33:25.969
Olivia.

33:25.971 --> 33:29.006
[ roberta flack's "will you
still love me tomorrow" plays ]

33:38.984 --> 33:42.886
♪ tonight you're mine ♪

33:42.888 --> 33:49.960
♪ completely ♪

33:49.962 --> 33:53.864
♪ you give your love ♪

33:53.866 --> 33:59.069
♪ so sweetly ♪

33:59.071 --> 34:02.672
♪ tonight ♪

34:02.674 --> 34:06.977
♪ the light of love ♪

34:06.979 --> 34:11.415
♪ is in your eyes ♪

34:11.417 --> 34:20.257
♪ but will you love me
tomorrow? ♪

34:21.760 --> 34:31.601
♪ is this a lasting treasure ♪

34:31.603 --> 34:41.511
♪ or just a moment's pleasure? ♪

34:41.513 --> 34:47.217
♪ can i believe ♪

34:47.219 --> 34:53.457
♪ the magic in your sighs? ♪

34:53.459 --> 35:04.201
♪ will you still love me
tomorrow? ♪

35:04.203 --> 35:14.044
♪ tonight with words unspoken ♪

35:14.046 --> 35:21.051
♪ you say
that i'm the only one ♪

35:29.061 --> 35:30.994
[ door opens ]

35:30.996 --> 35:32.496
Cyrus:
I see you got the news.

35:33.765 --> 35:35.765
Believe me, sir,

35:35.767 --> 35:38.301
I was as shocked...
As you are.

35:38.303 --> 35:41.004
Liv's pulled
her fair share of stunts.

35:41.006 --> 35:43.673
We all have,
but this is...

35:44.977 --> 35:48.111
So, here's what i'm thinking.
We talk to liv.

35:48.113 --> 35:50.447
Let her know that [sighs]

35:50.449 --> 35:52.616
We're not out to get her
because we aren't.

35:52.618 --> 35:55.418
Then if she's willing
to help us find her father,

35:55.420 --> 35:57.187
Put him back in prison --
no.

35:58.457 --> 35:59.656
I'm sorry?

35:59.658 --> 36:02.125
I want her released.

36:02.127 --> 36:04.828
Find some technicality,
whatever it takes.

36:04.830 --> 36:07.230
I want the charges dropped,
and i want her out of there.

36:09.168 --> 36:11.635
W-- wh--

36:11.637 --> 36:13.637
What did she say to you?

36:13.639 --> 36:17.374
Help me understand, sir.
Please.

36:17.376 --> 36:20.377
She told me there were people
trying to kill her father.

36:20.379 --> 36:22.746
And you believed her?

36:28.320 --> 36:30.820
[ groans ]

36:30.822 --> 36:33.156
What the hell's this?

36:33.158 --> 36:34.891
Langley sent it over
an hour ago.

36:34.893 --> 36:36.393
That soda factory
in bandar,

36:36.395 --> 36:38.695
The one liv said
to take a second look at,

36:38.697 --> 36:42.032
They're not
cooling uranium in there.

36:42.034 --> 36:44.534
They're cooling servers.

36:44.536 --> 36:47.370
Massive tianhe-2 supercomputers
they've been using

36:47.372 --> 36:50.240
To stage cyber attacks
against western targets.

36:50.242 --> 36:51.708
Sir?

36:51.710 --> 36:53.143
Her gut was right, cy.

36:53.145 --> 36:54.311
Her gut was right,

36:54.313 --> 36:56.813
And that translator
saved all our asses.

36:56.815 --> 36:58.648
I'm giving him asylum,
by the way.

36:58.650 --> 37:00.317
Least we can do.

37:00.319 --> 37:02.419
So, you think that just because
she was right about that --

37:02.421 --> 37:04.221
Who's to say she's not right
about her father?

37:04.223 --> 37:06.890
History and common sense.
That's what.

37:06.892 --> 37:09.759
Have her brought home to me
as soon as she's released.

37:09.761 --> 37:11.995
And by home,
i mean the residence,

37:11.997 --> 37:13.563
Not her apartment.

37:15.767 --> 37:17.367
And you can go now, cy.

37:17.369 --> 37:18.668
Sir, don't do this.

37:18.670 --> 37:20.103
I said you can go.

37:20.105 --> 37:22.105
For god sakes, fitz,
he killed your son!

37:24.776 --> 37:26.643
I forgave you, didn't i?

37:32.117 --> 37:34.918
Straight to the residence,
cyrus.

37:34.920 --> 37:37.220
No exceptions.

37:37.222 --> 37:39.089
Yes, sir.

37:41.226 --> 37:42.926
[ sighs ]

37:44.062 --> 37:46.129
[ camera shutters clicking ]

37:59.244 --> 38:01.478
In seven minutes,
an mq-1 predator

38:01.480 --> 38:03.580
Is gonna blow that
little soda factory of yours

38:03.582 --> 38:04.914
Off the map.

38:04.916 --> 38:06.850
And there's nothing you can do
to stop me.

38:12.557 --> 38:16.326
After 2 years, 8 months,
and 17 days of negotiations,

38:16.328 --> 38:18.662
The treaty that supposedly
could never have been signed

38:18.664 --> 38:20.664
Has finally been signed.

38:20.666 --> 38:23.066
Today, the white house
announced an historic accord

38:23.068 --> 38:25.568
With the nation of bandar.

38:27.806 --> 38:29.306
[ computer chimes ]

38:34.346 --> 38:36.079
[ computer pinging ]

38:44.690 --> 38:46.923
Jake: Mr. President,
it just came through, sir.

38:46.925 --> 38:49.092
Rowan's location.

38:54.199 --> 38:56.166
Let me know
when it's done.

38:56.168 --> 38:57.734
Jake: Yes, sir.

38:59.438 --> 39:02.172
♪♪

39:29.901 --> 39:31.334
[ camera shutter clicking ]

39:31.336 --> 39:35.171
[ cellphone vibrating
and ringing ]

39:35.173 --> 39:36.873
[ cellphone beeps ]

39:44.716 --> 39:47.050
[ cart rattling ]

40:01.867 --> 40:04.401
[ cellphone rings ]

40:04.403 --> 40:05.735
Mellie.

40:05.737 --> 40:07.270
Where the hell are you?

40:07.272 --> 40:08.505
I'm not coming.

40:08.507 --> 40:10.407
We had a meeting.
I'm not coming.

40:10.409 --> 40:12.375
I'm gonna tell fitz, liv.
Mellie.

40:12.377 --> 40:14.177
No, i warned you.
You cannot do this to me.

40:14.179 --> 40:15.445
I'm gonna tell him
what you did.

40:15.447 --> 40:17.414
Mellie,
i already told him.

40:17.416 --> 40:19.449
[ sighs ]

40:21.686 --> 40:23.853
[ cellphone beeps ]

40:32.230 --> 40:34.164
Fitz:
I called off jake.

40:37.068 --> 40:38.802
He's not gonna kill
your father.

40:38.804 --> 40:41.037
He's gonna bring him in.

40:55.954 --> 40:57.620
Fitz: Thank you.

40:59.090 --> 41:00.790
Thank you.

41:03.662 --> 41:04.828
Fitz.

41:04.830 --> 41:07.163
How you feeling?

41:07.165 --> 41:11.434
Fitz, what's going on?
These are my clothes.

41:11.436 --> 41:13.069
I had all your clothes
and belongings

41:13.071 --> 41:14.304
Packed up
and brought over.

41:14.306 --> 41:16.239
What are you talking about?
Why?

41:16.241 --> 41:17.640
Why?

41:17.642 --> 41:19.843
Because
you live here now.

41:24.082 --> 41:25.582
[ handcuffs rattle ]

41:25.584 --> 41:28.852
[ footsteps ]

41:33.191 --> 41:35.425
This is your home.

41:35.427 --> 41:37.193
I have a home.

41:39.164 --> 41:41.831
I am going to keep you safe,
olivia.

41:41.833 --> 41:44.801
Whatever it takes.

41:44.803 --> 41:47.103
I'm assigning you
a secret service detail,

41:47.105 --> 41:49.172
And you will live
here in the white house.

41:49.174 --> 41:52.542
This will be your home.

41:52.544 --> 41:54.677
You and i
will be together now,

41:54.679 --> 41:57.714
And you will be safe...

41:57.716 --> 41:59.215
And protected.

42:16.701 --> 42:20.937
Command.
I have some questions for you.

42:22.908 --> 42:24.073
[ camera shutter clicks ]

42:28.513 --> 42:31.548
♪♪
